    },
    {
      "id": "a3",
      "assumption": "useMarket also needs to be mocked because ContextRow calls useMarket(assignment.variableId) to fetch outcomes for the selected context market.",
      "confidence": 0.99,
      "if_wrong": "Without mocking useMarket, context rows won't have outcome options, and tests for selecting context outcomes will fail."
    },
    {
      "id": "a4",
      "assumption": "The mutation response shape is { order: { orderId: string } }, same as TradingPanel, because both use useProbabilityEdit which hits the same endpoint.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "if_wrong": "The success message test would render incorrectly. Would need to check the actual API response type."
    },
    {
      "id": "a5",
      "assumption": "crypto.randomUUID() works in the vitest/jsdom environment since TradingPanel tests already exercise the same code path without mocking it.",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "if_wrong": "Would need to add a global mock: vi.stubGlobal('crypto', { randomUUID: () => 'test-uuid' })."
    },
    {
      "id": "a6",
      "assumption": "The task scope covers: (1) unconfigured session guard, (2) rendering the form with outcome select and probability slider, (3) adding/removing context conditions, (4) selecting markets and outcomes in context rows, (5) submit payload with valid context, (6) pending/success/error states, (7) notation display updates.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "if_wrong": "Might be over- or under-testing. The task description says 'rendering variable list, outcome selection for conditionals, conditional context building' which maps to items 2-5."
    },
    {
      "id": "a7",
      "assumption": "The otherMarkets filtering (excluding current market, only active status) should be tested since it's core logic that determines which markets appear as context options.",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "if_wrong": "Might be considered an implementation detail not worth testing directly, but it's important for correctness."
    }
  ],
  "spawn_children": false,
  "children": []
}

